				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Once you go Bard, You Never Go Back - Some Tips you might not know<a name="53665"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 25 04 10:02 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Greetings all again<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Just sharing some of my experiences thus far in my EverQuest journey.  I'm level 40 now and I have convinced countless players that bards can be really good, valuable to a group, and fun to play.  Along the way, I have learned some things that I have not seen in the Guides or on the forum, so I will share them with you now.
<br />

<br />
Before I asked, <i>what's the best and fastest way to gain Defense?</i>
<br />

<br />
From my experience, the fastest and best way is for a shaman (might work with any class with a pet) where the pet was blue to me in this scenario, we went to a PvP Area and the shaman's pet attacked me.  I got an Agility buff from a high level shaman at PoK prior to this trial, and I started raising Defense skill incredibly fast while in the PvP area.  The blue pet only hit me sometimes for 1-2 damage so my health remained full without health regen song.  If your defense is low, I highly recommend giving this a try, this is by far the easiest and best method I have tried for raising your Defense Skill fast.
<br />

<br />
<i>Ever have a lore item, and wish you could loot another or buy another lore at the bazaar because its cheap and you can sell it for a profit?</i>
<br />

<br />
Well, there's a way.  You might know it, or you might not, but if it helps just 1 player out there, its worth it!<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  When you access your bank box, at the lower left corner there's 2 slots for shared banking.  Place your Lore item in there, and your character can then get another Lore item.
<br />

<br />
I put 2 Deluxe Tool Boxes in those slots because they can hold Giant items and have 10 slots each.  They only cost like a few pp and can be found in PoK.  A must have for your bank because they're so cheap and useful<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Because I'm from Morden Rasp, items are So expensive.  <i>So which items did I end up choosing?</i>
<br />

<br />
Well, at level 2 I got all my newbie bard gear.  It was very cheap, and some higher levels were more than happy to help me get some of the components I needed (I'm now pass their level <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /> Now at level 40, I either Quest for items such as the Earring of the Solstice which was pretty easy for me since you can buy all the components from PoK, or I buy either Required level or Recommended level armor.  This is because at Morden Rasp, there's a lot of players on the 30-day trial and there's a demand for twink items and good no lvl req items.  The only thing cheap seems to be the higher quality items, ironic.  The stats on the items I look for is AC, hp, and stamina.  I try to get some Cha if I can, but currently my Charisma is at 208 just with items.  The Cloak of Greater Pernicity and Crown of King Tranix really helped with the Cha<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
As for experience, my whole perception on Bard Kiting has done a 360.  I simply <b>LOVE it</b> now.  It seems I can gain as many levels a day as I want as long as I keep kiting<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  All I do is grab a temp and sow, and I'm off twisting Selos, DDD, and CoD with my Brass instrument equiped.  I level so fast I cannot even believe it.  All the loots.. all the coins, now this is the way to get some extra money!<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I have to admit, I love trading at the bazaar.  Leave your computer on over night with some good items priced cheaper than everyone else but still making a profit, and I wake up with thousands of pp just waiting for me to spend.  I take a lot of notes on the demand for certain items, and the range of prices of these items.  Easy way to make a lot of pp if you like Trading and willing to take notes to make sure you're making a profit.
<br />

<br />
I would like to thank everyone for their help and advice in my last post.  As for the auto forage skill and other skills, I made a macro that says:
<br />

<br />
/doability 1
<br />
/doability 2
<br />
/doability 3
<br />
/doability 4, pause 60
<br />
/autoinventory
<br />

<br />
I bound this to the right arrow, and now I gain skill in Disarm Traps, Pick Lock, Sense Traps, and Forage all day long while I play just by making a right turn<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I hope this helps someone, take care all!
<br />

<br />
Sincerely,
<br />
Ashlii
<br />
</span></td>
