				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Once you go Bard, You Never Go Back - Some Tips you might not know<a name="53727"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 26 04 7:48 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I strongly recommend taking the pause out of your macro, especially if you have it bound to a movement key rather than pressing it manually.  Here is why.
<br />

<br />
First, you cannot do anything else while that macro runs.  (You CAN interrupt a macro with the /time command, apparently).  You can't chat, start songs, nothing.
<br />

<br />
Second, there is simply no need to pause.  If you try to do a skill that has not refreshed, nothing happens.  That's all.  Nothing.  You don't get annoying spams, you don't get delays of any kind.  Just nothing.  The next time you hit your arrow key when that skill time HAS refreshed, it will go off like normal.
<br />

<br />
I use song macros, and while I was training stuff, I put them on my song macros.  Tracking I left on my selos key for a very long time, even after maxing it, simply minimizing the tracking window, so that whenever I need it, I re-expand the window, and it has already been refreshed recently.
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast 1
<br />
/doablility 1
<br />

<br />
Sense Heading (don't have to train this anymore, lol), Sense Traps, Disarm Traps, Forage, and Tracking can all be trained this way, without needing and &quot;object&quot; to work on.  I also trained Intimidation on a song macro while kiting.  (Good backup for fear kiting).  If you are chant kiting giants, for example, you are too far away for it to actually work, but the skill will still go up.  Be careful NOT to train Intimidation in regular xp groups on a song macro.  Train it manually on corpses or your friends in the group, hehe.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
