			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Once you go Bard, You Never Go Back - Some Tips you might not know<a name="53769"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 26 04 1:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Before I asked, what's the best and fastest way to gain Defense?</span></blockquote>
<br />
I agree with you on using a Shaman, beyond that, no I don't agree.  High level shaman, or at least one that can give you everybuff that a low level toon can have is preferable.  Fully buffed with HP, Dex, Agi, Sta, Regen and sow makes you much more formidible.  Having the shaman there to heal you as needed is also good.  Gotta love Torpor type heals.
<br />

<br />
Since the issue is raising skills being grouped with the shaman is not an issue.  Grouping allows the shaman to watch over you more easily and to HoT when you are getting low in HP.
<br />

<br />
Now, once buffed the best thing to do is find the mobs that will help raise your skills.  I prefer to do this prior to lvl 15 in FoB.  Start in the noob section with the scaled wolf pups, scorpions and beatles.  Get a lot of them and drag them to a safe point and have at them.
<br />
Do not use a high damage weapons; don't want to kill them off fast you know.  The max number of mobs that can hit you at a given time is 4.   When you have as many as possible hitting you for a long duration you will find your defense raising much faster.  Once you have maxed current level melee skills, disband from shaman and XP until ding, regroup with shaman and work on skill ups again, as before.  When the mobs go green in the noob section move to the close end ramp, not the noob ramp.  Go out and grab skellies, scorpions, bandits, and footpads and have at em.
<br />

<br />
Kerns castle is the next stop on the way for working up melee skills.  Skellies never run away.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, that's the basic idea.  It works very well.  I know, been there done that multiple times with and for my fiance.  She has a lvl 65 shaman, I have a lvl 58 shaman.
<br />

<br />
My favorite macro for increasing a skill is my begging macro.  It is specifically intended for use when doing melee.
<br />
<span class="Highlight">/attack off
<br />
/doability 1
<br />
/attack on</span>
<br />
I keep the actual begging key in my hotkeys so I can see when it is ready to fire off again.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I though I'd share. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" /></span></td>
